## Optimization Strategies

### Strategy 1: Filter External Dependencies

Don't show `node_modules` by default - they clutter the graph:

```javascript
// Backend: When creating edges
async createEdge(fromFile, dependency) {
  const resolvedPath = await this.resolvePath(dependency.module, fromFile);
  
  // Skip node_modules
  if (dependency.type === 'node_module' && !this.config.showNodeModules) {
    return null;
  }
  
  // ... rest of code
}
```

### Strategy 2: Hierarchical Edge Bundling

For files with many dependencies, group edges:

```javascript
// Frontend: Group edges by type
const groupedEdges = edges.reduce((acc, edge) => {
  const key = `${edge.source}_${edge.type}`;
  if (!acc[key]) acc[key] = [];
  acc[key].push(edge);
  return acc;
}, {});

// Show count badge instead of individual edges
{Object.entries(groupedEdges).map(([key, edges]) => {
  if (edges.length > 5) {
    return <EdgeBundle edges={edges} />;
  }
  return edges.map(e => <Edge {...e} />);
})}
```

### Strategy 3: Progressive Disclosure

Only show edges when hovering:

```javascript
// This matches your current hover-to-preview logic!

const visibleEdges = useMemo(() => {
  if (!hoveredNode) {
    return [];  // No edges shown by default
  }
  
  // Show only edges connected to hovered node
  return edges.filter(edge => 
    edge.source === hoveredNode || edge.target === hoveredNode
  );
}, [hoveredNode, edges]);

<ReactFlow edges={visibleEdges} />
```

